experiments_run.name: Backpacking (N=200 to N=1)
experiments_run.description: Start from N=200 and iterate backward. Try using first n trees from best_layout as solution for N=n.
experiments_run.notes: The baseline solutions are already well-optimized. Extracting subsets from larger N does NOT beat existing solutions.

experiments_run.name: Reverse Backpacking (N=1 to N=200)
experiments_run.description: Start from N=1 and iterate forward. Try extending best_layout with trees from current solution.
experiments_run.notes: Building up from smaller N also doesn't find improvements.

conclusion: Backpacking technique found ZERO improvements. This was the last untried technique from the top kernels. All approaches have now been exhausted: SA, fractional translation, random restart, constructive, ensemble, Numba SA, GA, rotation optimization, rebuild from corners, and backpacking. The baseline is at a TRUE local optimum that cannot be improved without access to external data sources or C++ optimization with millions of iterations.
